

	 
      118 days to go. another  depressing  day.   a mother in the foodcourt, sharing a plate of chicken rice with  her two sons. unable to afford another, they buy another plate, a plate of plain rice.   opposite their table, two teenage girls with their plates half full. they rose to leave.  the newspaper spoke of a the tale of young innocent children, scavaging the rubbish dump to put food on the table while the other end of the earth plays a movie of a man, overstuffed with Macdonalds.   someone mentioned, life is unfair. hard irony, it's true isn't it? peace, love, warmth -- have they all become nothing but myths?
    
